paragraphs.title: Show current tables and Count
paragraphs.text:
from pyspark.sql import Row 
tables = [dict(table=tableName, count=sqlContext.table(tableName).count()) for tableName, isTemp in sqlContext.tables().collect() if isTemp==False]
#sqlContext.createDataFrame(tables).registerTempTable("table_info")

print "%table\nTable\tCount"
for row in tables:
    print "\t".join([row["table"],str(row["count"])])

result.msg:
Table	Count
features	1563
user_features	39132
user_scores	71476
video_features	6376
videos	2468

paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT Count(*) as Available_Records
FROM user_scores u, videos v
WHERE u.videoId = v.videoId

paragraphs.title: Videos
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT * FROM videos
order by startAt

result.msg:
channels	description	endAt	imageUrl	length	processed	startAt	title	videoId	videoUrl

GROUP BY v.videoId, v.title

paragraphs.title: Video's features
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT v.videoId, v.title, vf.feature, vf.score 
FROM videos v, video_features vf
WHERE v.videoId = vf.videoId and v.videoId = ${videoId=1}

paragraphs.title: Features Count
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT vf.feature, count(*) as count 
FROM videos v, video_features vf
WHERE v.videoId = vf.videoId
GROUP BY vf.feature
ORDER BY count(*) DESC
